#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
CLI for interacting with ollama run gemma4:e4b.
Supports file I/O, @ file references (fzf), shell tools, and a task queue.

Usage:
  python ollama_chat.py                          # interactive chat
  python ollama_chat.py -p "summarise this" -f input.txt
  python ollama_chat.py -p "translate" -f doc.txt -o out.txt
  python ollama_chat.py --tasks                  # run pending tasks from DB

Keyboard shortcuts (interactive mode):
  ^E     : Open current prompt in $EDITOR (useful for multi-line messages)
  ^U     : Clear the current line
  ^C     : Cancel and start a new prompt

@ references (interactive mode):
  Type @ to open fzf and pick files. Each Enter selection adds the file
  to the message without submitting the prompt, allowing you to:
    - Add multiple files: @file1 some text @file2 more text
    - Mix files and regular text: diff @ vs @
    - Continue editing after each file selection

Tool use:
  The model can run shell commands and write files.
  Permissions are checked before every tool call:
    - ask        : prompt each time
    - session    : allow for this run only
    - global     : persisted to ~/.ollama_chat_perms.json

  Examples of what you might globally allow:
    ls, git log, git status, git diff

  Examples that should stay as 'ask':
    git commit, git push, rm, write_file

Task queue:
  The model can call task_add / task_done / task_list to manage a
  SQLite task list (~/.ollama_chat_tasks.db).  Use --tasks to run all
  pending tasks autonomously.
"""

